    "actor_description": "It stops me. My breath catches halfway in and doesn't want to finish. The world suddenly feels too large to hold in a single thought-like something has opened above me and I'm staring straight into it. My body goes quiet without asking permission: hands useless at my sides, tongue blank, heart thudding slow and heavy. I feel small, but not crushed-more like I've been reminded, with absolute clarity, that I'm standing inside something vast.",
    "description_text": "{actor} goes still as if a switch has been flipped-head tipped, gaze fixed upward or outward, lips parted a fraction. Their blinking slows; their hands hang where they are, forgetting their next motion. Even their breathing seems to pause, the moment held in a tight, quiet suspension.",
    "alternate_descriptions": {
        "auditory": "I hear a single soft intake of breath, then a hush-no fidgeting, no speech-like someone's sound has been turned down to make room for what they're sensing.",
        "tactile": "I sense someone becoming unnaturally still. The air feels steadier, as if their movement has stopped so completely it changes the texture of the space."
    },
